{"id":"barrel","term":"Barrel","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A vessel used for keeping flour (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 17:12\">1 Kings 17:12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 17:14\">14</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 17:16\">16</a>). The same word (cad) so rendered is also translated “pitcher,” a vessel for carrying water (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 24:14\">Gen. 24:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 7:16\">Judg. 7:16</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Kings 17:12","1 Kings 17:14","1 Kings 17:16","Genesis 24:14","Judges 7:16"]}